                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>96(1)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48, 56, 57, 58, 60, 61, and 63 of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>96(2)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48, 51, 56, 57, 58, 60, 61, 63 of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>96(3)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 56 and 63 of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>96(4)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Section 26 and 56 of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 97</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Access to numbers and services</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>97(1)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Cross cutting -: obliges member states, where feasible, to ensure end-users are able to access all numbers within the EU and access services using non-geographic numbers. </p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 58 and 57(1) of the Communications Act 2003 along with Ofcom’s general conditions</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>97(2)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48, 51(1), 51(2)(f) of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 98</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Exemption of certain microenterprises</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Not required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>99</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Non-Discrimination</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Section 51(2)(b) of the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 100</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Fundamental rights safeguard</p>
              </td>
