            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 101</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Level of harmonisation</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Not required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 102</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Information requirements for contracts</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and 51of the Communications Act 2003. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 102 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>102(6)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
