            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>102(7)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Transposition not required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 103</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Transparency, comparison of offers and publication of information</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 26, 45 to 48, 51(1)(a) of the Communications Act 2003.  Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 103 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>103(4)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Transposition not required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 104</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Quality of service related to internet access services and publicly available interpersonal communication services</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48, 51(1) and 135 to 137 of the Communications Act 2003. This provision is transposed by Ofcom using their existing powers to set general conditions under the Communications Act 2003</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 105 (1) to (4)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Contract duration and termination</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and 51 of the Communications Act 2003. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 105 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>105(5)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Consumer Rights Act 2015</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>105(6)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and 51 of the Communications Act 2003. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 105 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes. Section 124U(1) and (2)  and 124W of the Communications Act 2003, as inserted by paragraph 54 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>105(7)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Section 124U(3) of the Communications Act 2003, as inserted by paragraph 54 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 106</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Provider switching and number portability </p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and 51 of the Communications Act 2003. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 106 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 107</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Bundled offers</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>107(1)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and 51(1), (2)(ba) and (8) and (9) of the Communications Act 2003 (as inserted by paragraph 19 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations) and by sections 124U(4) and 124W of that Act (as inserted by paragraph 54 of that Schedule). Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 107 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>107(2)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
