              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>107(3)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48 and section 51(1), (2)(ba) and (8) and (9) of the Communications Act 2003, as inserted by paragraph 19 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 107 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>107(4)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Sections 45 to 48, section 51(1), (8) and (9) (as inserted by paragraph 19 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations) and section 124U(4), as inserted by paragraph 54 of Schedule 1 to the draft regulations. Ofcom consulted on making amendments to the relevant general conditions which implement Article 107 in its December 2019 Consultation entitled: ‘Fair treatment and easier switching for broadband and mobile customers, Proposals to implement the new European Electronic Communications Code’ and will publish a statement confirming the changes</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
